COMMENTS. — Two young males were brought back to 
Paris
(É. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire & F. Cuvier 1824 [1824-1842]: Vol. 2, Text to pl.; 
Girard 1856: 119
). Species referred to as 
Ombatte Kingiensis
[sic, 
nomen nudum
] from King Island in Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle; 
Péron (1804a)
refered to this taxon.

